<edge source="World Athletics Federation" target="Noah Carter">
  <data key="d7">37.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Noah Carter’s relationship with the World Athletics Federation involves a rigorous oversight process that ensures his athletic achievements, particularly his new 100-meter sprint world record set at championship events, are officially recognized and validated according to established rules and regulations. The federation plays a pivotal role in managing the validation of such performances by athletes like Noah Carter during these high-profile competitions.

The World Athletics Federation is responsible for confirming and validating the legitimacy of any records set by athletes under strict rules and regulations enforced by the organization. This includes overseeing the validation process for new records achieved during championships to ensure compliance with governing standards. The federation's role extends beyond just validation; it also ensures the integrity and fairness of athletic achievements at championship levels, maintaining a high level of scrutiny over record-setting performances.

Furthermore, the World Athletics Federation manages the rules and regulations that athletes like Noah Carter must adhere to during their participation in these events. This involves ensuring all record-breaking performances are officially recognized according to established norms and contributing to the maintenance of integrity and fairness within the sport. The federation plays an integral part in confirming the legitimacy of performances by athletes who compete under its oversight.

In summary, the World Athletics Federation is crucial for overseeing Noah Carter’s achievements and adherence to athletic regulations during championship events. This involves validating new records, ensuring compliance with governing standards, and maintaining the overall integrity and fairness of athletic performances at the highest levels.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees the validation of records set by athletes like Noah Carter at major championships.</data>
  <data key="d9">athlete governance,athlete oversight,athlete performance oversight,athlete recognition,athlete regulation,athlete supervision,governance,governing body,oversight,record validation,regulation,validation</data>
